Append a compact JSONL entry to ``results/raki-history.jsonl`` after every ``raki run`` so metric trends can be tracked across evaluation runs without post-processing full JSON reports. Each line records ``run_id``, ``timestamp``, ``session_count``, ``aggregate_scores``, and ``manifest_hash``. Use ``--history-file PATH`` to write to a custom location, or ``--no-history`` to skip the log entirely.
